'''Inventory''', initially known as the '''Gallery''' before being renamed in June 2025, is a feature that allows users to manage their [[emojis]], [[stickers]], [[items]], and more. The inventory currently includes six types of content: icons, photos, emojis, stickers, prints, and items. Some inventory tabs require an active [[VRC+]] subscription to manage items.

== Content type ==
=== Photo Gallery ===
The '''Photo Gallery''' is where custom photos are located. Photos can serve multiple purposes, such as an additional profile picture option on a user's profile. They can also be used when sending invites to other users. Photos can also be used to change the banner for a [[Groups|group]], and add to the group's gallery. The Photo Gallery is available exclusively to active VRC+ subscribers. Users have a limit of 64 photos that can be saved.

=== Prints ===
''See also [[Prints|Prints]] for more detailed information.''[[File:Gallery_Prints.webp|thumb|A print of 2 ghosts surrounding a user.]]
'''Prints''' are photos users can take within VRChat and spawn as an object in-world for other users to share and save. Prints carry metadata of: who took the photo, where, and when a photo was taken. They can also have custom messages written on them. Prints have the same appearance as real-world [[Wikipedia:Instant_film|instant films]]. All prints will always upload in 1080p resolution. Users can "collect" other user's prints by saving them to their inventory. 

Non-VRC+ users can save up to 20 prints, while users with an active VRC+ subscription can save up to 64 prints and are able to drop them.

=== User Icons ===
[[File:VRChat_Plus_Icons.webp|thumb|right|Icons can be displayed on a user's nameplate if they have access to their icon inventory.]]'''User Icons''' are custom images used as a user's icon on their in-game [[Nameplates|nameplate]]. User Icons is available exclusively to active VRC+ subscribers. Users have a limit of 64 icons that can be saved. When [[Streamer Mode]] is enabled, all other user's icons will be hidden.

=== Emoji ===
''See also [[Emojis]] for more detailed information.''[[File:Wow.webp|thumb|100px|The "Wow" emoji.]]
'''Emoji''' in the inventory are custom, user-uploadable emoji. Users with an active VRC+ subscription can upload up to 18 custom emojis, including the option to create animated emojis using sprite sheets. When creating an emoji, you can choose one of several animations.

==== Animated emoji ====
'''Animated emoji''' are emoji that contain a moving picture, similar to that of a GIF. This is possible by uploading your emoji as a sprite sheet. In addition, you can have your animated emoji use one of the above animations listed below.

==== Animations ====
When uploading an emoji, you have to select an animation that fits the emoji.

Fifteen of the animation names are tied to a pre-existing default emoji animations. For example, any emoji using the "Mistletoe" animation will share the same type of animation as the Mistletoe in the Winter page of the Default Emoji pack. However, there are twelve unique animations also added to the emoji creator.

