=== Stickers ===
''See also [[Stickers]] for more detailed information.''[[File:2-VaultCat.webp|thumb|100px|The "Vault Cat" sticker.]]'''Stickers''' in the inventory are images that users can upload and place in an [[Instances|instance]]. Stickers can be placed on almost any surface in a world for all users in the instance to see. Only one sticker may be placed by each user at a time, and stickers will automatically disappear when the user leaves the instance. Users with an active VRC+ subscription can upload up to 18 custom stickers.

=== Items ===
''See also [[Special:MyLanguage/Items|Items]] for more detailed information.''
[[File:THE_REFERENCE_CUBE_item_original.png|thumb|100px|A image of "THE REFERENCE CUBE" item.]]
'''Items''' are objects that users can spawn within a world. Items can take the place of toys, tools, gadgets, etc. World creators can disable items in their world if they wish.

=== Cosmetics ===
'''Cosmetics''' include Drone, and Portal skins, Warp Effects, and UI decorations like themes and backgrounds.

====Drones====
[[File:Drone Trace Drone.png|100px|thumb|The "Trace Drone".]]
''See also [[Special:MyLanguage/Camera Drone|Drone]] for more detailed information.''

Drone cosmetics include drone skins, each one is unique and can be customized via it's palette. Drone Palette customization is a VRC+ feature, which allows the user to change the Primary, Secondary, and Trail of the Drone.

====Portals====
[[File:Portal B3-7A Portal.png|100px|thumb|The "B3-7A Portal".]]
''See also [[Special:MyLanguage/Portals|Portal]] for more detailed information.''

Portal cosmetics include portal skins, each having it's own custom model. Portal skins have unique opening & closing animations, aswell as sounds.

====Warp Effects====
''See also [[Special:MyLanguage/Warp Effects|Warp Effects]] for more detailed information.''

Warp Effects are custom animations that play on your [[Avatars|avatar]] when you join or leave an instance. 

