Emojis, stickers and items can belong to collections, which can be used to filter the Inventory.

List of known collections:

* Pride Month 2025
* Summer 2025

==Uploading==
User icons, photos, emoji, stickers, or prints can be taken and uploaded within the client via the [[Camera|camera's]] "Camera Mode" options. They can also be uploaded on the VRChat website via their respective pages.

* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/photos|Photos}}
* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/user-icons|User Icons}}
* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/emojis/custom|Emoji}}
* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/stickers/custom|Stickers}}

===Upload requirements===
[[File:DancingBirdSprite.png|200px|thumb|right|An example of a sprite sheet for a 10-frame animated emoji.]]
When uploading files to be used as user icons, photos, emoji, stickers, or prints, on the VRChat website, they must meet the following criteria:

*Must be less than 10MB
*Larger than 64x64 pixels
*Icons and Photos must be smaller than 2048x2048 pixels
*Emojis and Stickers must be smaller than 1024x1024 pixels

When uploading Animated Emoji, images should be 1024x1024 with square frames in a uniform grid, ordered left to right, then top to bottom. You can preset animation values in advance using the file name, like so'':''

*''ExampleEmoji_14frames_10fps.png''

The "Enable Sprite Sheet Mode" option must be checked for images to animate.

